1
00:00:09,875 --> 00:00:13,625
Once upon a time, there was a creature named Wynn

2
00:00:13,625 --> 00:00:17,333
lost in the deep, where cold currents creep.

3
00:00:17,333 --> 00:00:21,083
He had no memories, no sky, no shore.

4
00:00:21,083 --> 00:00:25,625
Only endless water and nowhere to belong.

5
00:00:26,875 --> 00:00:28,291
One day 

6
00:00:28,291 --> 00:00:30,750
he drifted against a jar tangled in the sand.

7
00:00:32,916 --> 00:00:36,291
Inside, a swirl of silent eyes

8
00:00:36,291 --> 00:00:41,458
each holding a world, a life, a sky.

9
00:00:41,458 --> 00:00:43,583
When Wynn touched the glass

10
00:00:43,583 --> 00:00:46,041
visions poured through.

11
00:00:46,041 --> 00:00:47,666
Fields in bloom

12
00:00:47,666 --> 00:00:49,291
skies of blue

13
00:00:49,291 --> 00:00:50,375
laughter

14
00:00:50,375 --> 00:00:51,583
running

15
00:00:51,583 --> 00:00:52,791
falling rain.

16
00:00:52,791 --> 00:00:55,208
All the things he had never known

17
00:00:55,208 --> 00:00:57,916
and all the colors he had never seen.

18
00:00:59,208 --> 00:01:02,125
Carrying the jar through the endless blue

19
00:01:02,125 --> 00:01:03,833
Wynn realized

20
00:01:03,833 --> 00:01:06,958
he wasn't just seeing others’ memories

21
00:01:06,958 --> 00:01:10,083
he was gathering dreams for his own.

22
00:01:10,708 --> 00:01:14,375
And when he placed the jar atop a coral tower

23
00:01:14,375 --> 00:01:17,208
the memories drifted into the sea

24
00:01:17,208 --> 00:01:19,416
painting the darkness with light

25
00:01:19,416 --> 00:01:22,000
with color, with song.

26
00:01:22,500 --> 00:01:25,875
Wind smiled for the first time.

27
00:01:25,875 --> 00:01:27,666
He wasn't lost anymore.

28
00:01:27,666 --> 00:01:30,625
He had made a world of his own.
